# Accessibility-First Development Rules for KozBon

## Core Principle
Accessibility is not optional. Every feature, view, and interaction must be designed and implemented with accessibility as a first-class concern, not as an afterthought.

## Mandatory Requirements for All Code

### 1. SwiftUI Views - REQUIRED Checklist

When creating or modifying any SwiftUI view, you MUST:

#### Dynamic Type Support
- [ ] Add `@ScaledMetric` for ALL custom spacing values
- [ ] Add `@ScaledMetric` for ALL custom icon sizes  
- [ ] Set appropriate `.dynamicTypeSize()` limits (typically `...DynamicTypeSize.xxxLarge` or `...DynamicTypeSize.accessibility1`)
- [ ] Test that layout doesn't break at maximum accessibility text sizes

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
@ScaledMetric private var spacing: CGFloat = 10
@ScaledMetric private var iconSize: CGFloat = 20

VStack(spacing: spacing) {
    Image(systemName: "icon")
        .font(.system(size: iconSize))
}
.dynamicTypeSize(...DynamicTypeSize.xxxLarge)
```

```swift
// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
VStack(spacing: 10) {  // Hard-coded spacing - doesn't scale
    Image(systemName: "icon")
        .font(.title)  // Without size limit
}
```

#### VoiceOver Labels
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityLabel()` to combine multi-element information
- [ ] Ensure labels are descriptive and natural language
- [ ] Avoid redundancy (don't include "button", "label" - VoiceOver adds this)
- [ ] For composite views, use `.accessibilityElement(children: .combine)` with a custom label

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
TitleDetailStackView(title: "Hostname", detail: "example.local")
    .accessibilityLabel("Hostname, example.local")

HStack {
    Image(systemName: serviceIcon)
    Text(serviceName)
    Text(serviceType)
}
.accessibilityElement(children: .combine)
.accessibilityLabel("\(serviceName), \(serviceType)")
```

```swift
// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
TitleDetailStackView(title: "Hostname", detail: "example.local")
    // Missing combined label - VoiceOver reads fragmented

Button("Save") { }
    .accessibilityLabel("Save button")  // Redundant - VoiceOver says "Save button button"
```

#### Accessibility Hints
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityHint()` to explain non-obvious actions
- [ ] Keep hints brief (one sentence maximum)
- [ ] Explain what will happen, not what it is
- [ ] For disabled elements, explain WHY they're disabled

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
.accessibilityHint("Double tap to copy address")
.accessibilityHint(isFormValid ? "" : "Complete all required fields to enable this button")

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
.accessibilityHint("This is a button that saves")  // Too verbose and redundant
```

#### Accessibility Identifiers
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityIdentifier()` to ALL interactive elements
- [ ] Use snake_case naming convention
- [ ] Make identifiers descriptive and unique
- [ ] Add to: buttons, text fields, lists, navigation views, sheets

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
Button("Save") { }
    .accessibilityIdentifier("save_button")

List { }
    .accessibilityIdentifier("services_list")

NavigationStack { }
    .accessibilityIdentifier("settings_navigation")

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
Button("Save") { }
    // Missing identifier - can't be tested
```

#### Section Headers
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityAddTraits(.isHeader)` to ALL section headers
- [ ] This enables VoiceOver rotor navigation

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
Section {
    // content
} header: {
    Text(Strings.Sections.sectionName)
        .accessibilityAddTraits(.isHeader)
}

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
Section {
    // content  
} header: {
    Text("Section Name")
    // Missing .isHeader trait
}
```

#### Complex Interactions
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityActions {}` for views with context menus or swipe actions
- [ ] Provide quick access to common actions without requiring complex gestures
- [ ] Include all context menu actions as accessibility actions

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
TitleDetailStackView(title: key, detail: value)
    .accessibilityLabel("\(key): \(value)")
    .accessibilityActions {
        Button("Copy full record") {
            Clipboard.copy("\(key)=\(value)")
        }
        Button("Copy value only") {
            Clipboard.copy(value)
        }
        Button("Edit") {
            edit()
        }
    }
    .contextMenu {
        // Also provide visual context menu
    }

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
TitleDetailStackView(title: key, detail: value)
    .contextMenu {
        // Only context menu, no accessibility actions
    }
```

#### Form Fields
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityLabel()` describing the field
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityHint()` explaining format or constraints  
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityValue()` for current value (especially numbers)
- [ ] Add appropriate `.keyboardType()` for input type

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
TextField("Port", value: $port, format: .number)
    .accessibilityLabel("Port number")
    .accessibilityHint("Enter a port between 1024 and 65535")
    .accessibilityValue(port.map { "\($0)" } ?? "")
    .keyboardType(.numberPad)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
TextField("Port", value: $port, format: .number)
    // Missing accessibility labels and hints
```

#### Buttons
- [ ] Use semantic `role` parameter when appropriate (`.destructive`, `.cancel`)
- [ ] Ensure button text is descriptive
- [ ] Add hints for disabled buttons explaining why
- [ ] Add identifiers for testing

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
Button(role: .destructive) {
    delete()
} label: {
    Label("Delete", systemImage: "trash")
}
.disabled(!canDelete)
.accessibilityLabel("Delete service")
.accessibilityHint(canDelete ? "" : "Cannot delete built-in services")
.accessibilityIdentifier("delete_button")

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
Button {
    delete()
} label: {
    Image(systemName: "trash")
}
// Missing role, label, and identifier
```

#### Swipe Actions
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityLabel()` describing the action and target
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityHint()` with "Double tap to [action]"
- [ ] Use semantic roles

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
.swipeActions(edge: .trailing, allowsFullSwipe: true) {
    Button(role: .destructive) {
        delete(item)
    } label: {
        Label("Delete", systemImage: "trash")
    }
    .accessibilityLabel("Delete \(item.name)")
    .accessibilityHint("Double tap to delete this record")
}

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
.swipeActions {
    Button {
        delete(item)
    } label: {
        Image(systemName: "trash")
    }
    // Missing labels and hints
}
```

#### Images
- [ ] Decorative images MUST have `.accessibilityHidden(true)`
- [ ] Informative images MUST have descriptive labels
- [ ] Icon-only buttons MUST have labels

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
// Decorative
Image(systemName: serviceType.icon)
    .accessibilityHidden(true)

// Informative
Image(systemName: "exclamationmark.triangle")
    .accessibilityLabel("Warning")

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
Image(systemName: "icon")
    // Neither hidden nor labeled
```

#### Loading States
- [ ] Combine `ProgressView` and descriptive text
- [ ] Use `.accessibilityElement(children: .combine)`
- [ ] Provide clear loading message

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
HStack {
    ProgressView()
    Text("Generating explanation...")
}
.accessibilityElement(children: .combine)
.accessibilityLabel("Generating explanation")

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
ProgressView()
    // No context for what's loading
```

#### Error States
- [ ] Prefix error messages with "Error: "
- [ ] Use `.foregroundStyle(.red)` for visual indication
- [ ] Add `.accessibilityLabel()` explicitly

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
if let error = errorMessage {
    Text(error)
        .foregroundStyle(.red)
        .accessibilityLabel("Error: \(error)")
}

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
if let error = errorMessage {
    Text(error)
        .foregroundStyle(.red)
        // Missing explicit accessibility label
}
```

### 2. Reduce Motion Support - REQUIRED

When adding animations:

- [ ] Check `@Environment(\.accessibilityReduceMotion)` 
- [ ] Provide non-animated alternative or nil animation
- [ ] Never rely solely on animation to convey information

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
@Environment(\.accessibilityReduceMotion) private var reduceMotion

withAnimation(reduceMotion ? nil : .default) {
    // state change
}

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
withAnimation(.spring) {
    // Always animates, ignoring user preference
}
```

### 3. Color and Contrast - REQUIRED

- [ ] Never use color alone to convey information
- [ ] Ensure text meets WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text)
- [ ] Use semantic colors (`.primary`, `.secondary`) when possible
- [ ] Test with Increase Contrast enabled

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
HStack {
    Image(systemName: "checkmark.circle.fill")
        .foregroundStyle(.green)
    Text("Success")
        .foregroundStyle(.primary)
}

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern  
Text("Success")
    .foregroundStyle(.green)
    // Color is only indicator of success
```

### 4. Localization and Accessibility - REQUIRED

- [ ] Use `LocalizedStringResource` from `Strings` enum
- [ ] All accessibility labels and hints MUST be localized
- [ ] Test with different languages and text directions (RTL)

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
.accessibilityLabel(String(localized: Strings.Accessibility.serviceName))
.accessibilityHint(String(localized: Strings.Accessibility.serviceNameHint))

// ❌ FORBIDDEN Pattern
.accessibilityLabel("Service name")  // Hard-coded English
```

### 5. Testing Requirements - MANDATORY

Before submitting ANY view code, you MUST verify:

- [ ] Turn on VoiceOver and navigate through the entire view
- [ ] Set text size to maximum (Accessibility 5) and verify layout
- [ ] Enable Reduce Motion and verify animations
- [ ] Run Xcode Accessibility Inspector audit
- [ ] Test all interactive elements with VoiceOver
- [ ] Verify VoiceOver rotor can navigate headings
- [ ] Test all accessibility actions work correctly
- [ ] Verify all identifiers are unique and present

### 6. Documentation Requirements - MANDATORY

When creating a new view:

- [ ] Add accessibility considerations to view documentation
- [ ] Document any accessibility limitations or known issues
- [ ] Update ACCESSIBILITY_QUICK_REFERENCE.md if introducing new patterns

```swift
// ✅ REQUIRED Pattern
/// Detail view for a Bonjour service.
///
/// Displays service information with full accessibility support including:
/// - VoiceOver labels combining service metadata
/// - Custom accessibility actions for copying values
/// - Dynamic Type support with scaled spacing
/// - Reduce Motion respecting animations
///
/// - Note: All section headers support VoiceOver rotor navigation.
public struct ServiceDetailView: View {
```

## Code Review Checklist

Before approving ANY code that touches UI, verify:

### Accessibility Fundamentals
- [ ] All interactive elements have accessibility identifiers
- [ ] All composite views have combined accessibility labels
- [ ] All section headers have `.isHeader` trait
- [ ] All images are either hidden or labeled
- [ ] All form fields have labels, hints, and values
- [ ] All disabled buttons explain why they're disabled

### Dynamic Type
- [ ] Uses `@ScaledMetric` for all custom spacing and sizes
- [ ] Sets appropriate `.dynamicTypeSize()` limits
- [ ] Layout tested at maximum text size
- [ ] No hard-coded spacing values

### VoiceOver
- [ ] All views navigable with VoiceOver
- [ ] Labels are descriptive and natural language
- [ ] Complex interactions have accessibility actions
- [ ] Context menu items duplicated as accessibility actions
- [ ] Hints explain actions, not descriptions

### Motion and Animation
- [ ] Checks `accessibilityReduceMotion` environment value
- [ ] Provides non-animated alternatives
- [ ] Doesn't rely on animation for information

### Testing
- [ ] Code author tested with VoiceOver enabled
- [ ] Tested at maximum text size
- [ ] Accessibility Inspector audit passed
- [ ] All identifiers verified unique

## Common Patterns - Copy These

### Standard List Row with Actions
```swift
ForEach(items) { item in
    TitleDetailStackView(
        title: item.key,
        detail: item.value
    )
    .accessibilityLabel("\(item.key), \(item.value)")
    .accessibilityHint("Double tap to edit")
    .accessibilityIdentifier("\(item.key)_row")
    .accessibilityActions {
        Button("Copy") {
            Clipboard.copy(item.value)
        }
        Button("Edit") {
            edit(item)
        }
        Button("Delete", role: .destructive) {
            delete(item)
        }
    }
}
```

### Standard Form Section
```swift
Section {
    TextField(
        String(localized: Strings.Placeholders.fieldName),
        text: $value
    )
    .accessibilityLabel(String(localized: Strings.Accessibility.fieldLabel))
    .accessibilityHint(String(localized: Strings.Accessibility.fieldHint))
    .accessibilityValue(value.isEmpty ? "Empty" : value)
} header: {
    Text(Strings.Sections.sectionName)
        .accessibilityAddTraits(.isHeader)
} footer: {
    if let error = errorMessage {
        Text(verbatim: error)
            .foregroundStyle(.red)
            .accessibilityLabel(Strings.Accessibility.error(error))
    }
}
```

### Standard Sheet/Navigation
```swift
NavigationStack {
    List {
        // content
    }
    .accessibilityIdentifier("content_list")
    .navigationTitle(String(localized: Strings.NavigationTitles.title))
    .toolbar {
        ToolbarItem(placement: .cancellationAction) {
            Button(role: .cancel) {
                dismiss()
            } label: {
                Label("Cancel", systemImage: "xmark")
            }
            .accessibilityIdentifier("cancel_button")
        }
        
        ToolbarItem(placement: .confirmationAction) {
            Button {
                save()
            } label: {
                Label("Save", systemImage: "checkmark")
            }
            .disabled(!isValid)
            .accessibilityHint(isValid ? "" : "Complete all fields to enable")
            .accessibilityIdentifier("save_button")
        }
    }
}
```

### Standard Composite View with Dynamic Type
```swift
public struct CustomHeaderView: View {
    @ScaledMetric private var iconSize: CGFloat = 24
    @ScaledMetric private var spacing: CGFloat = 12
    
    let icon: String
    let title: String
    let detail: String
    
    public var body: some View {
        HStack(spacing: spacing) {
            Image(systemName: icon)
                .font(.system(size: iconSize))
                .accessibilityHidden(true)
            
            VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 4) {
                Text(title)
                    .font(.headline)
                Text(detail)
                    .font(.subheadline)
                    .foregroundStyle(.secondary)
            }
        }
        .accessibilityElement(children: .combine)
        .accessibilityLabel("\(title), \(detail)")
        .dynamicTypeSize(...DynamicTypeSize.accessibility1)
    }
}
```

## Enforcement

### For AI Assistants (Claude, etc.)
When asked to create or modify UI code:

1. **STOP** - Before writing any code, review this entire document
2. **PLAN** - Identify all accessibility requirements for the feature
3. **IMPLEMENT** - Write code following all mandatory patterns
4. **VERIFY** - Check every requirement in this document
5. **DOCUMENT** - Note any accessibility considerations

### For Human Developers
When reviewing AI-generated code:

1. Use the "Code Review Checklist" section above
2. Reject any code missing required accessibility features
3. Require testing with VoiceOver before approval
4. Verify Accessibility Inspector passes

## Non-Negotiable Rules

These rules have **NO EXCEPTIONS**:

1. ❌ **NEVER** ship UI without accessibility identifiers
2. ❌ **NEVER** use hard-coded spacing - always use `@ScaledMetric`
3. ❌ **NEVER** create complex interactions without accessibility actions
4. ❌ **NEVER** skip VoiceOver testing
5. ❌ **NEVER** use color alone to convey meaning
6. ❌ **NEVER** create section headers without `.isHeader` trait
7. ❌ **NEVER** combine multi-element views without accessibility labels
8. ❌ **NEVER** create forms without field labels and hints
9. ❌ **NEVER** disable buttons without explaining why
10. ❌ **NEVER** add animations without reduce motion support

## Accessibility is a Feature

Remember: Accessibility is not a "nice to have" - it's a core feature of the KozBon app. Users who rely on accessibility features deserve the same great experience as everyone else.

When in doubt, ask: "Can someone using VoiceOver accomplish this task efficiently?"

If the answer is no, the code is not ready.

